b"While most can shelter at home safely, some can't. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
That\xe2\x80\x99s why we are partnering with domestic violence organizations and local governments in 35 cities across 16 countries to provide 50,000 free rides to shelters and safe spaces, and more than 45,000 free meals.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
As the global COVID-19 pandemic continues to impact our communities, stay-at-home orders have created unintended challenges for some of the most vulnerable among us, including victims of domestic violence. Many are facing increased risk, and are left with few safe options to access resources, seek help or plan an exit. \xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
A few weeks ago, we pledged to provide 10 million free rides and food deliveries to those who need them most during this unprecedented time. With experts reporting a surge in domestic violence globally in the last few weeks, many shelters and service providers are seeking urgent assistance. We want to do our part to help survivors access life-saving services and find a safe place to shelter.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
We\xe2\x80\x99ve expanded longstanding partnerships and initiated new ones with incredible organizations like the Safe Center LI in New York, Femmes Avec in Paris (@femmes_avec_), WESNET in Australia (@WESNETAustralia), Nissa Institute for Women\xe2\x80\x99s Development in Johannesburg , YWCA in Canada (@ywcacanada) and so many more. We\xe2\x80\x99re extremely grateful for their tireless efforts to support our communities during this especially difficult time.\xe2\xa0\x80
\xe2\xa0\x80
Uber is committed to women\xe2\x80\x99s safety both on our app and in the communities that we serve. Over the past several years, we\xe2\x80\x99ve partnered with leading gender-based violence organizations globally on awareness, education and prevention of sexual assault and domestic violence. We\xe2\x80\x99ve also taken important steps \xe2\x80\x93 like publishing the industry\xe2\x80\x99s first-ever safety report \xe2\x80\x93 to drive accountability and improve safety for Uber and the entire industry.\xe2\xa0\x80 \xe2\xa0\x80
Each of us can help others access resources and safe spaces. If you need help, or know someone who does, there are resources available through our partners at @nomoreorg and the @nnedv."

b'\xe2\x80\x9cI wanted to find a way to feed the people that are in the most danger right now, those in the ER and in the COVID unit.\xe2\x80\x9d\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
After hearing from a nurse that the staff at a local hospital were too busy to eat, Tammy, driver in Tennessee, decided to do something about it. She launched a local fundraiser to help buy meals for the hospital staff. So far Tammy has helped raise over $18,000 in donations and made 31 deliveries to keep her local healthcare workers fed. \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3
:camera_with_flash:Larry Kuzniewsk'
